@philipJFpfahl  what hash are you using of Cardinal? Can you show me
git log

and copy-paste the first couple lines here?

@philipJFpfahl can you perhaps try
export LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/lib:$LIBRARY_PATH
cd cardinal
rm -rf build install
make -j8

@pshriwise do you know what is the correct way to find gsl?

If it's a system installation, it should be found automatically. I pulled this version of gsl-lite (or as close as I could get, I didn't see a v0.36.1 here: https://github.com/gsl-lite/gsl-lite/releases) and I didn't run into any issues.
Going into the /build/openmc directory and running make clean; make VERBOSE=1 | tee omc_verbose_make.txt might be helpful to see all of the explicit paths used to look for headers during compilation -- could be some hints there.
@philipJFpfahl once you've done that, can you up load the file here?
